129static vpx_codec_err_t update_error_state(
130 vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx, const struct vpx_internal_error_info *error) {
131 const vpx_codec_err_t res = error->error_code;
132
133 if (res != VPX_CODEC_OK)
134 ctx->base.err_detail = error->has_detail ? error->detail : NULL;
135
136 return res;
137}

139#undef ERROR
140#define ERROR(str) \
141 do { \
142 ctx->base.err_detail = str; \
143 return VPX_CODEC_INVALID_PARAM; \
144 } while (0)
145
146#define RANGE_CHECK(p, memb, lo, hi) \
147 do { \
148 if (!(((p)->memb == (lo) || (p)->memb > (lo)) && (p)->memb <= (hi))) \
149 ERROR(#memb " out of range [" #lo ".." #hi "]"); \
150 } while (0)
151
152#define RANGE_CHECK_HI(p, memb, hi) \
153 do { \
154 if (!((p)->memb <= (hi))) ERROR(#memb " out of range [.." #hi "]"); \
155 } while (0)
156
157#define RANGE_CHECK_LO(p, memb, lo) \
158 do { \
159 if (!((p)->memb >= (lo))) ERROR(#memb " out of range [" #lo "..]"); \
160 } while (0)
161
162#define RANGE_CHECK_BOOL(p, memb) \
163 do { \
164 if (!!((p)->memb) != (p)->memb) ERROR(#memb " expected boolean"); \
165 } while (0)

167static vpx_codec_err_t validate_config(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
168 const vpx_codec_enc_cfg_t *cfg,
169 const struct vp9_extracfg *extra_cfg) {
170 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, g_w, 1, 65535); // 16 bits available
171 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, g_h, 1, 65535); // 16 bits available
172 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, g_timebase.den, 1, 1000000000);
173 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, g_timebase.num, 1, 1000000000);
174 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, g_profile, 3);
175
176 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_max_quantizer, 63);
177 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_min_quantizer, cfg->rc_max_quantizer);
178 RANGE_CHECK_BOOL(extra_cfg, lossless);
179 RANGE_CHECK_BOOL(extra_cfg, frame_parallel_decoding_mode);
180 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, aq_mode, 0, AQ_MODE_COUNT - 2);
181 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, alt_ref_aq, 0, 1);
182 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, frame_periodic_boost, 0, 1);
183 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, g_threads, 64);
184 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, g_lag_in_frames, MAX_LAG_BUFFERS);
185 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, rc_end_usage, VPX_VBR, VPX_Q);
186 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_undershoot_pct, 100);
187 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_overshoot_pct, 100);
188 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_2pass_vbr_bias_pct, 100);
189 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, rc_2pass_vbr_corpus_complexity, 0, 10000);
190 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, kf_mode, VPX_KF_DISABLED, VPX_KF_AUTO);
191 RANGE_CHECK_BOOL(cfg, rc_resize_allowed);
192 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_dropframe_thresh, 100);
193 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_resize_up_thresh, 100);
194 RANGE_CHECK_HI(cfg, rc_resize_down_thresh, 100);
195#if CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
196 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, g_pass, VPX_RC_ONE_PASS, VPX_RC_ONE_PASS);
197#else
198 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, g_pass, VPX_RC_ONE_PASS, VPX_RC_LAST_PASS);
199#endif
200 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, min_gf_interval, 0, (MAX_LAG_BUFFERS - 1));
201 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, max_gf_interval, 0, (MAX_LAG_BUFFERS - 1));
202 if (extra_cfg->max_gf_interval > 0) {
203 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, max_gf_interval, 2, (MAX_LAG_BUFFERS - 1));
204 }
205 if (extra_cfg->min_gf_interval > 0 && extra_cfg->max_gf_interval > 0) {
206 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, max_gf_interval, extra_cfg->min_gf_interval,
207 (MAX_LAG_BUFFERS - 1));
208 }
209
210 // For formation of valid ARF groups lag_in _frames should be 0 or greater
211 // than the max_gf_interval + 2
212 if (cfg->g_lag_in_frames > 0 && extra_cfg->max_gf_interval > 0 &&
213 cfg->g_lag_in_frames < extra_cfg->max_gf_interval + 2) {
214 ERROR("Set lag in frames to 0 (low delay) or >= (max-gf-interval + 2)");
215 }
216
217 if (cfg->rc_resize_allowed == 1) {
218 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, rc_scaled_width, 0, cfg->g_w);
219 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, rc_scaled_height, 0, cfg->g_h);
220 }
221
222 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, ss_number_layers, 1, VPX_SS_MAX_LAYERS);
223 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, ts_number_layers, 1, VPX_TS_MAX_LAYERS);
224
225 {
226 unsigned int level = extra_cfg->target_level;
227 if (level != LEVEL_1 && level != LEVEL_1_1 && level != LEVEL_2 &&
228 level != LEVEL_2_1 && level != LEVEL_3 && level != LEVEL_3_1 &&
229 level != LEVEL_4 && level != LEVEL_4_1 && level != LEVEL_5 &&
230 level != LEVEL_5_1 && level != LEVEL_5_2 && level != LEVEL_6 &&
231 level != LEVEL_6_1 && level != LEVEL_6_2 && level != LEVEL_UNKNOWN &&
232 level != LEVEL_AUTO && level != LEVEL_MAX)
233 ERROR("target_level is invalid");
234 }
235
236 if (cfg->ss_number_layers * cfg->ts_number_layers > VPX_MAX_LAYERS)
237 ERROR("ss_number_layers * ts_number_layers is out of range");
238 if (cfg->ts_number_layers > 1) {
239 unsigned int sl, tl;
240 for (sl = 1; sl < cfg->ss_number_layers; ++sl) {
241 for (tl = 1; tl < cfg->ts_number_layers; ++tl) {
242 const int layer = LAYER_IDS_TO_IDX(sl, tl, cfg->ts_number_layers);
243 if (cfg->layer_target_bitrate[layer] <
244 cfg->layer_target_bitrate[layer - 1])
245 ERROR("ts_target_bitrate entries are not increasing");
246 }
247 }
248
249 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, ts_rate_decimator[cfg->ts_number_layers - 1], 1, 1);
250 for (tl = cfg->ts_number_layers - 2; tl > 0; --tl)
251 if (cfg->ts_rate_decimator[tl - 1] != 2 * cfg->ts_rate_decimator[tl])
252 ERROR("ts_rate_decimator factors are not powers of 2");
253 }
254
255 // VP9 does not support a lower bound on the keyframe interval in
256 // automatic keyframe placement mode.
257 if (cfg->kf_mode != VPX_KF_DISABLED && cfg->kf_min_dist != cfg->kf_max_dist &&
258 cfg->kf_min_dist > 0)
259 ERROR(
260 "kf_min_dist not supported in auto mode, use 0 "
261 "or kf_max_dist instead.");
262
263 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, row_mt, 0, 1);
264 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, motion_vector_unit_test, 0, 2);
265 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, enable_auto_alt_ref, 0, MAX_ARF_LAYERS);
266 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, cpu_used, -9, 9);
267 RANGE_CHECK_HI(extra_cfg, noise_sensitivity, 6);
268 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, tile_columns, 0, 6);
269 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, tile_rows, 0, 2);
270 RANGE_CHECK_HI(extra_cfg, sharpness, 7);
271 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, arnr_max_frames, 0, 15);
272 RANGE_CHECK_HI(extra_cfg, arnr_strength, 6);
273 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, cq_level, 0, 63);
274 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, g_bit_depth, VPX_BITS_8, VPX_BITS_12);
275 RANGE_CHECK(cfg, g_input_bit_depth, 8, 12);
276 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, content, VP9E_CONTENT_DEFAULT,
277 VP9E_CONTENT_INVALID - 1);
278
279#if !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
280 if (cfg->g_pass == VPX_RC_LAST_PASS) {
281 const size_t packet_sz = sizeof(FIRSTPASS_STATS);
282 const int n_packets = (int)(cfg->rc_twopass_stats_in.sz / packet_sz);
283 const FIRSTPASS_STATS *stats;
284
285 if (cfg->rc_twopass_stats_in.buf == NULL)
286 ERROR("rc_twopass_stats_in.buf not set.");
287
288 if (cfg->rc_twopass_stats_in.sz % packet_sz)
289 ERROR("rc_twopass_stats_in.sz indicates truncated packet.");
290
291 if (cfg->ss_number_layers > 1 || cfg->ts_number_layers > 1) {
292 int i;
293 unsigned int n_packets_per_layer[VPX_SS_MAX_LAYERS] = { 0 };
294
295 stats = cfg->rc_twopass_stats_in.buf;
296 for (i = 0; i < n_packets; ++i) {
297 const int layer_id = (int)stats[i].spatial_layer_id;
298 if (layer_id >= 0 && layer_id < (int)cfg->ss_number_layers) {
299 ++n_packets_per_layer[layer_id];
300 }
301 }
302
303 for (i = 0; i < (int)cfg->ss_number_layers; ++i) {
304 unsigned int layer_id;
305 if (n_packets_per_layer[i] < 2) {
306 ERROR(
307 "rc_twopass_stats_in requires at least two packets for each "
308 "layer.");
309 }
310
311 stats = (const FIRSTPASS_STATS *)cfg->rc_twopass_stats_in.buf +
312 n_packets - cfg->ss_number_layers + i;
313 layer_id = (int)stats->spatial_layer_id;
314
315 if (layer_id >= cfg->ss_number_layers ||
316 (unsigned int)(stats->count + 0.5) !=
317 n_packets_per_layer[layer_id] - 1)
318 ERROR("rc_twopass_stats_in missing EOS stats packet");
319 }
320 } else {
321 if (cfg->rc_twopass_stats_in.sz < 2 * packet_sz)
322 ERROR("rc_twopass_stats_in requires at least two packets.");
323
324 stats =
325 (const FIRSTPASS_STATS *)cfg->rc_twopass_stats_in.buf + n_packets - 1;
326
327 if ((int)(stats->count + 0.5) != n_packets - 1)
328 ERROR("rc_twopass_stats_in missing EOS stats packet");
329 }
330 }
331#endif // !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
332
333#if !CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
334 if (cfg->g_profile > (unsigned int)PROFILE_1) {
335 ERROR("Profile > 1 not supported in this build configuration");
336 }
337#endif
338 if (cfg->g_profile <= (unsigned int)PROFILE_1 &&
339 cfg->g_bit_depth > VPX_BITS_8) {
340 ERROR("Codec high bit-depth not supported in profile < 2");
341 }
342 if (cfg->g_profile <= (unsigned int)PROFILE_1 && cfg->g_input_bit_depth > 8) {
343 ERROR("Source high bit-depth not supported in profile < 2");
344 }
345 if (cfg->g_profile > (unsigned int)PROFILE_1 &&
346 cfg->g_bit_depth == VPX_BITS_8) {
347 ERROR("Codec bit-depth 8 not supported in profile > 1");
348 }
349 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, color_space, VPX_CS_UNKNOWN, VPX_CS_SRGB);
350 RANGE_CHECK(extra_cfg, color_range, VPX_CR_STUDIO_RANGE, VPX_CR_FULL_RANGE);
351 return VPX_CODEC_OK;
352}

354static vpx_codec_err_t validate_img(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
355 const vpx_image_t *img) {
356 switch (img->fmt) {
357 case VPX_IMG_FMT_YV12:
358 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I420:
359 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I42016:
360 case VPX_IMG_FMT_NV12: break;
361 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I422:
362 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I444:
363 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I440:
364 if (ctx->cfg.g_profile != (unsigned int)PROFILE_1) {
365 ERROR(
366 "Invalid image format. I422, I444, I440, NV12 images are "
367 "not supported in profile.");
368 }
369 break;
370 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I42216:
371 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I44416:
372 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I44016:
373 if (ctx->cfg.g_profile != (unsigned int)PROFILE_1 &&
374 ctx->cfg.g_profile != (unsigned int)PROFILE_3) {
375 ERROR(
376 "Invalid image format. 16-bit I422, I444, I440 images are "
377 "not supported in profile.");
378 }
379 break;
380 default:
381 ERROR(
382 "Invalid image format. Only YV12, I420, I422, I444 images are "
383 "supported.");
384 break;
385 }
386
387 if (img->d_w != ctx->cfg.g_w || img->d_h != ctx->cfg.g_h)
388 ERROR("Image size must match encoder init configuration size");
389
390 return VPX_CODEC_OK;
391}

393static int get_image_bps(const vpx_image_t *img) {
394 switch (img->fmt) {
395 case VPX_IMG_FMT_YV12:
396 case VPX_IMG_FMT_NV12:
397 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I420: return 12;
398 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I422: return 16;
399 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I444: return 24;
400 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I440: return 16;
401 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I42016: return 24;
402 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I42216: return 32;
403 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I44416: return 48;
404 case VPX_IMG_FMT_I44016: return 32;
405 default: assert(0 && "Invalid image format"); break;
406 }
407 return 0;
408}

410// Modify the encoder config for the target level.
411static void config_target_level(VP9EncoderConfig *oxcf) {
412 double max_average_bitrate; // in bits per second
413 int max_over_shoot_pct;
414 const int target_level_index = get_level_index(oxcf->target_level);
415
416 vpx_clear_system_state();
417 assert(target_level_index >= 0);
418 assert(target_level_index < VP9_LEVELS);
419
420 // Maximum target bit-rate is level_limit * 80%.
421 max_average_bitrate =
422 vp9_level_defs[target_level_index].average_bitrate * 800.0;
423 if ((double)oxcf->target_bandwidth > max_average_bitrate)
424 oxcf->target_bandwidth = (int64_t)(max_average_bitrate);
425 if (oxcf->ss_number_layers == 1 && oxcf->pass != 0)
426 oxcf->ss_target_bitrate[0] = (int)oxcf->target_bandwidth;
427
428 // Adjust max over-shoot percentage.
429 max_over_shoot_pct =
430 (int)((max_average_bitrate * 1.10 - (double)oxcf->target_bandwidth) *
431 100 / (double)(oxcf->target_bandwidth));
432 if (oxcf->over_shoot_pct > max_over_shoot_pct)
433 oxcf->over_shoot_pct = max_over_shoot_pct;
434
435 // Adjust worst allowed quantizer.
436 oxcf->worst_allowed_q = vp9_quantizer_to_qindex(63);
437
438 // Adjust minimum art-ref distance.
439 // min_gf_interval should be no less than min_altref_distance + 1,
440 // as the encoder may produce bitstream with alt-ref distance being
441 // min_gf_interval - 1.
442 if (oxcf->min_gf_interval <=
443 (int)vp9_level_defs[target_level_index].min_altref_distance) {
444 oxcf->min_gf_interval =
445 (int)vp9_level_defs[target_level_index].min_altref_distance + 1;
446 // If oxcf->max_gf_interval == 0, it will be assigned with a default value
447 // in vp9_rc_set_gf_interval_range().
448 if (oxcf->max_gf_interval != 0) {
449 oxcf->max_gf_interval =
450 VPXMAX(oxcf->max_gf_interval, oxcf->min_gf_interval);
451 }
452 }
453
454 // Adjust maximum column tiles.
455 if (vp9_level_defs[target_level_index].max_col_tiles <
456 (1 << oxcf->tile_columns)) {
457 while (oxcf->tile_columns > 0 &&
458 vp9_level_defs[target_level_index].max_col_tiles <
459 (1 << oxcf->tile_columns))
460 --oxcf->tile_columns;
461 }
462}

464static vpx_rational64_t get_g_timebase_in_ts(vpx_rational_t g_timebase) {
465 vpx_rational64_t g_timebase_in_ts;
466 g_timebase_in_ts.den = g_timebase.den;
467 g_timebase_in_ts.num = g_timebase.num;
468 g_timebase_in_ts.num *= TICKS_PER_SEC;
469 reduce_ratio(&g_timebase_in_ts);
470 return g_timebase_in_ts;
471}

473static vpx_codec_err_t set_encoder_config(
474 VP9EncoderConfig *oxcf, vpx_codec_enc_cfg_t *cfg,
475 const struct vp9_extracfg *extra_cfg) {
476 const int is_vbr = cfg->rc_end_usage == VPX_VBR;
477 int sl, tl;
478 unsigned int raw_target_rate;
479 oxcf->profile = cfg->g_profile;
480 oxcf->max_threads = (int)cfg->g_threads;
481 oxcf->width = cfg->g_w;
482 oxcf->height = cfg->g_h;
483 oxcf->bit_depth = cfg->g_bit_depth;
484 oxcf->input_bit_depth = cfg->g_input_bit_depth;
485 // TODO(angiebird): Figure out if we can just use g_timebase to indicate the
486 // inverse of framerate
487 // guess a frame rate if out of whack, use 30
488 oxcf->init_framerate = (double)cfg->g_timebase.den / cfg->g_timebase.num;
489 if (oxcf->init_framerate > 180) oxcf->init_framerate = 30;
490 oxcf->g_timebase = cfg->g_timebase;
491 oxcf->g_timebase_in_ts = get_g_timebase_in_ts(oxcf->g_timebase);
492
493 oxcf->mode = GOOD;
494
495 switch (cfg->g_pass) {
496 case VPX_RC_ONE_PASS: oxcf->pass = 0; break;
497 case VPX_RC_FIRST_PASS: oxcf->pass = 1; break;
498 case VPX_RC_LAST_PASS: oxcf->pass = 2; break;
499 }
500
501 oxcf->lag_in_frames =
502 cfg->g_pass == VPX_RC_FIRST_PASS ? 0 : cfg->g_lag_in_frames;
503 oxcf->rc_mode = cfg->rc_end_usage;
504
505 raw_target_rate =
506 (unsigned int)((int64_t)oxcf->width * oxcf->height * oxcf->bit_depth * 3 *
507 oxcf->init_framerate / 1000);
508 // Cap target bitrate to raw rate
509 cfg->rc_target_bitrate = VPXMIN(raw_target_rate, cfg->rc_target_bitrate);
510
511 // Convert target bandwidth from Kbit/s to Bit/s
512 oxcf->target_bandwidth = 1000 * (int64_t)cfg->rc_target_bitrate;
513 oxcf->rc_max_intra_bitrate_pct = extra_cfg->rc_max_intra_bitrate_pct;
514 oxcf->rc_max_inter_bitrate_pct = extra_cfg->rc_max_inter_bitrate_pct;
515 oxcf->gf_cbr_boost_pct = extra_cfg->gf_cbr_boost_pct;
516
517 oxcf->best_allowed_q =
518 extra_cfg->lossless ? 0 : vp9_quantizer_to_qindex(cfg->rc_min_quantizer);
519 oxcf->worst_allowed_q =
520 extra_cfg->lossless ? 0 : vp9_quantizer_to_qindex(cfg->rc_max_quantizer);
521 oxcf->cq_level = vp9_quantizer_to_qindex(extra_cfg->cq_level);
522 oxcf->fixed_q = -1;
523
524 oxcf->under_shoot_pct = cfg->rc_undershoot_pct;
525 oxcf->over_shoot_pct = cfg->rc_overshoot_pct;
526
527 oxcf->scaled_frame_width = cfg->rc_scaled_width;
528 oxcf->scaled_frame_height = cfg->rc_scaled_height;
529 if (cfg->rc_resize_allowed == 1) {
530 oxcf->resize_mode =
531 (oxcf->scaled_frame_width == 0 || oxcf->scaled_frame_height == 0)
532 ? RESIZE_DYNAMIC
533 : RESIZE_FIXED;
534 } else {
535 oxcf->resize_mode = RESIZE_NONE;
536 }
537
538 oxcf->maximum_buffer_size_ms = is_vbr ? 240000 : cfg->rc_buf_sz;
539 oxcf->starting_buffer_level_ms = is_vbr ? 60000 : cfg->rc_buf_initial_sz;
540 oxcf->optimal_buffer_level_ms = is_vbr ? 60000 : cfg->rc_buf_optimal_sz;
541
542 oxcf->drop_frames_water_mark = cfg->rc_dropframe_thresh;
543
544 oxcf->two_pass_vbrbias = cfg->rc_2pass_vbr_bias_pct;
545 oxcf->two_pass_vbrmin_section = cfg->rc_2pass_vbr_minsection_pct;
546 oxcf->two_pass_vbrmax_section = cfg->rc_2pass_vbr_maxsection_pct;
547 oxcf->vbr_corpus_complexity = cfg->rc_2pass_vbr_corpus_complexity;
548
549 oxcf->auto_key =
550 cfg->kf_mode == VPX_KF_AUTO && cfg->kf_min_dist != cfg->kf_max_dist;
551
552 oxcf->key_freq = cfg->kf_max_dist;
553
554 oxcf->speed = abs(extra_cfg->cpu_used);
555 oxcf->encode_breakout = extra_cfg->static_thresh;
556 oxcf->enable_auto_arf = extra_cfg->enable_auto_alt_ref;
557 if (oxcf->bit_depth == VPX_BITS_8) {
558 oxcf->noise_sensitivity = extra_cfg->noise_sensitivity;
559 } else {
560 // Disable denoiser for high bitdepth since vp9_denoiser_filter only works
561 // for 8 bits.
562 oxcf->noise_sensitivity = 0;
563 }
564 oxcf->sharpness = extra_cfg->sharpness;
565
566 vp9_set_first_pass_stats(oxcf, &cfg->rc_twopass_stats_in);
567
568#if CONFIG_FP_MB_STATS
569 oxcf->firstpass_mb_stats_in = cfg->rc_firstpass_mb_stats_in;
570#endif
571
572 oxcf->color_space = extra_cfg->color_space;
573 oxcf->color_range = extra_cfg->color_range;
574 oxcf->render_width = extra_cfg->render_width;
575 oxcf->render_height = extra_cfg->render_height;
576 oxcf->arnr_max_frames = extra_cfg->arnr_max_frames;
577 oxcf->arnr_strength = extra_cfg->arnr_strength;
578 oxcf->min_gf_interval = extra_cfg->min_gf_interval;
579 oxcf->max_gf_interval = extra_cfg->max_gf_interval;
580
581 oxcf->tuning = extra_cfg->tuning;
582 oxcf->content = extra_cfg->content;
583
584 oxcf->tile_columns = extra_cfg->tile_columns;
585
586 oxcf->enable_tpl_model = extra_cfg->enable_tpl_model;
587
588 // TODO(yunqing): The dependencies between row tiles cause error in multi-
589 // threaded encoding. For now, tile_rows is forced to be 0 in this case.
590 // The further fix can be done by adding synchronizations after a tile row
591 // is encoded. But this will hurt multi-threaded encoder performance. So,
592 // it is recommended to use tile-rows=0 while encoding with threads > 1.
593 if (oxcf->max_threads > 1 && oxcf->tile_columns > 0)
594 oxcf->tile_rows = 0;
595 else
596 oxcf->tile_rows = extra_cfg->tile_rows;
597
598 oxcf->error_resilient_mode = cfg->g_error_resilient;
599 oxcf->frame_parallel_decoding_mode = extra_cfg->frame_parallel_decoding_mode;
600
601 oxcf->aq_mode = extra_cfg->aq_mode;
602 oxcf->alt_ref_aq = extra_cfg->alt_ref_aq;
603
604 oxcf->frame_periodic_boost = extra_cfg->frame_periodic_boost;
605
606 oxcf->ss_number_layers = cfg->ss_number_layers;
607 oxcf->ts_number_layers = cfg->ts_number_layers;
608 oxcf->temporal_layering_mode =
609 (enum vp9e_temporal_layering_mode)cfg->temporal_layering_mode;
610
611 oxcf->target_level = extra_cfg->target_level;
612
613 oxcf->row_mt = extra_cfg->row_mt;
614 oxcf->motion_vector_unit_test = extra_cfg->motion_vector_unit_test;
615
616 oxcf->delta_q_uv = extra_cfg->delta_q_uv;
617
618 for (sl = 0; sl < oxcf->ss_number_layers; ++sl) {
619 for (tl = 0; tl < oxcf->ts_number_layers; ++tl) {
620 oxcf->layer_target_bitrate[sl * oxcf->ts_number_layers + tl] =
621 1000 * cfg->layer_target_bitrate[sl * oxcf->ts_number_layers + tl];
622 }
623 }
624 if (oxcf->ss_number_layers == 1 && oxcf->pass != 0) {
625 oxcf->ss_target_bitrate[0] = (int)oxcf->target_bandwidth;
626 }
627 if (oxcf->ts_number_layers > 1) {
628 for (tl = 0; tl < VPX_TS_MAX_LAYERS; ++tl) {
629 oxcf->ts_rate_decimator[tl] =
630 cfg->ts_rate_decimator[tl] ? cfg->ts_rate_decimator[tl] : 1;
631 }
632 } else if (oxcf->ts_number_layers == 1) {
633 oxcf->ts_rate_decimator[0] = 1;
634 }
635
636 if (get_level_index(oxcf->target_level) >= 0) config_target_level(oxcf);
637 // vp9_dump_encoder_config(oxcf, stderr);
638 return VPX_CODEC_OK;
639}

641static vpx_codec_err_t encoder_set_config(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
642 const vpx_codec_enc_cfg_t *cfg) {
643 vpx_codec_err_t res;
644 int force_key = 0;
645
646 if (cfg->g_w != ctx->cfg.g_w || cfg->g_h != ctx->cfg.g_h) {
647 if (cfg->g_lag_in_frames > 1 || cfg->g_pass != VPX_RC_ONE_PASS)
648 ERROR("Cannot change width or height after initialization");
649 if (!valid_ref_frame_size(ctx->cfg.g_w, ctx->cfg.g_h, cfg->g_w, cfg->g_h) ||
650 (ctx->cpi->initial_width && (int)cfg->g_w > ctx->cpi->initial_width) ||
651 (ctx->cpi->initial_height && (int)cfg->g_h > ctx->cpi->initial_height))
652 force_key = 1;
653 }
654
655 // Prevent increasing lag_in_frames. This check is stricter than it needs
656 // to be -- the limit is not increasing past the first lag_in_frames
657 // value, but we don't track the initial config, only the last successful
658 // config.
659 if (cfg->g_lag_in_frames > ctx->cfg.g_lag_in_frames)
660 ERROR("Cannot increase lag_in_frames");
661
662 res = validate_config(ctx, cfg, &ctx->extra_cfg);
663
664 if (res == VPX_CODEC_OK) {
665 ctx->cfg = *cfg;
666 set_encoder_config(&ctx->oxcf, &ctx->cfg, &ctx->extra_cfg);
667 // On profile change, request a key frame
668 force_key |= ctx->cpi->common.profile != ctx->oxcf.profile;
669 vp9_change_config(ctx->cpi, &ctx->oxcf);
670 }
671
672 if (force_key) ctx->next_frame_flags |= VPX_EFLAG_FORCE_KF;
673
674 return res;
675}

904static vpx_codec_err_t encoder_init(vpx_codec_ctx_t *ctx,
905 vpx_codec_priv_enc_mr_cfg_t *data) {
906 vpx_codec_err_t res = VPX_CODEC_OK;
907 (void)data;
908
909 if (ctx->priv == NULL) {
910 vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *const priv = vpx_calloc(1, sizeof(*priv));
911 if (priv == NULL) return VPX_CODEC_MEM_ERROR;
912
913 ctx->priv = (vpx_codec_priv_t *)priv;
914 ctx->priv->init_flags = ctx->init_flags;
915 ctx->priv->enc.total_encoders = 1;
916 priv->buffer_pool = (BufferPool *)vpx_calloc(1, sizeof(BufferPool));
917 if (priv->buffer_pool == NULL) return VPX_CODEC_MEM_ERROR;
918
919 if (ctx->config.enc) {
920 // Update the reference to the config structure to an internal copy.
921 priv->cfg = *ctx->config.enc;
922 ctx->config.enc = &priv->cfg;
923 }
924
925 priv->extra_cfg = default_extra_cfg;
926 once(vp9_initialize_enc);
927
928 res = validate_config(priv, &priv->cfg, &priv->extra_cfg);
929
930 if (res == VPX_CODEC_OK) {
931 priv->pts_offset_initialized = 0;
932 // TODO(angiebird): Replace priv->timestamp_ratio by
933 // oxcf->g_timebase_in_ts
934 priv->timestamp_ratio = get_g_timebase_in_ts(priv->cfg.g_timebase);
935
936 set_encoder_config(&priv->oxcf, &priv->cfg, &priv->extra_cfg);
937#if CONFIG_VP9_HIGHBITDEPTH
938 priv->oxcf.use_highbitdepth =
939 (ctx->init_flags & VPX_CODEC_USE_HIGHBITDEPTH) ? 1 : 0;
940#endif
941 priv->cpi = vp9_create_compressor(&priv->oxcf, priv->buffer_pool);
942 if (priv->cpi == NULL) res = VPX_CODEC_MEM_ERROR;
943 }
944 }
945
946 return res;
947}

951 vp9_remove_compressor(ctx->cpi);

953 vpx_free(ctx);
954 return VPX_CODEC_OK;
955}

957static void pick_quickcompress_mode(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
958 unsigned long duration,
959 unsigned long deadline) {
960 MODE new_mode = BEST;
961
962#if CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
963 (void)duration;
964 deadline = VPX_DL_REALTIME;
965#else
966 switch (ctx->cfg.g_pass) {
967 case VPX_RC_ONE_PASS:
968 if (deadline > 0) {
969 // Convert duration parameter from stream timebase to microseconds.
970 uint64_t duration_us;
971
972 VPX_STATIC_ASSERT(TICKS_PER_SEC > 1000000 &&
973 (TICKS_PER_SEC % 1000000) == 0);
974
975 duration_us = duration * (uint64_t)ctx->timestamp_ratio.num /
976 (ctx->timestamp_ratio.den * (TICKS_PER_SEC / 1000000));
977
978 // If the deadline is more that the duration this frame is to be shown,
979 // use good quality mode. Otherwise use realtime mode.
980 new_mode = (deadline > duration_us) ? GOOD : REALTIME;
981 } else {
982 new_mode = BEST;
983 }
984 break;
985 case VPX_RC_FIRST_PASS: break;
986 case VPX_RC_LAST_PASS: new_mode = deadline > 0 ? GOOD : BEST; break;
987 }
988#endif // CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
989
990 if (deadline == VPX_DL_REALTIME) {
991 ctx->oxcf.pass = 0;
992 new_mode = REALTIME;
993 }
994
995 if (ctx->oxcf.mode != new_mode) {
996 ctx->oxcf.mode = new_mode;
997 vp9_change_config(ctx->cpi, &ctx->oxcf);
998 }
999}

1001// Turn on to test if supplemental superframe data breaks decoding
1002// #define TEST_SUPPLEMENTAL_SUPERFRAME_DATA
1003static int write_superframe_index(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx) {
1004 uint8_t marker = 0xc0;
1005 unsigned int mask;
1006 int mag, index_sz;
1007
1008 assert(ctx->pending_frame_count);
1009 assert(ctx->pending_frame_count <= 8);
1010
1011 // Add the number of frames to the marker byte
1012 marker |= ctx->pending_frame_count - 1;
1013
1014 // Choose the magnitude
1015 for (mag = 0, mask = 0xff; mag < 4; mag++) {
1016 if (ctx->pending_frame_magnitude < mask) break;
1017 mask <<= 8;
1018 mask |= 0xff;
1019 }
1020 marker |= mag << 3;
1021
1022 // Write the index
1023 index_sz = 2 + (mag + 1) * ctx->pending_frame_count;
1024 if (ctx->pending_cx_data_sz + index_sz < ctx->cx_data_sz) {
1025 uint8_t *x = ctx->pending_cx_data + ctx->pending_cx_data_sz;
1026 int i, j;
1027#ifdef TEST_SUPPLEMENTAL_SUPERFRAME_DATA
1028 uint8_t marker_test = 0xc0;
1029 int mag_test = 2; // 1 - 4
1030 int frames_test = 4; // 1 - 8
1031 int index_sz_test = 2 + mag_test * frames_test;
1032 marker_test |= frames_test - 1;
1033 marker_test |= (mag_test - 1) << 3;
1034 *x++ = marker_test;
1035 for (i = 0; i < mag_test * frames_test; ++i)
1036 *x++ = 0; // fill up with arbitrary data
1037 *x++ = marker_test;
1038 ctx->pending_cx_data_sz += index_sz_test;
1039 printf("Added supplemental superframe data\n");
1040#endif
1041
1042 *x++ = marker;
1043 for (i = 0; i < ctx->pending_frame_count; i++) {
1044 unsigned int this_sz = (unsigned int)ctx->pending_frame_sizes[i];
1045
1046 for (j = 0; j <= mag; j++) {
1047 *x++ = this_sz & 0xff;
1048 this_sz >>= 8;
1049 }
1050 }
1051 *x++ = marker;
1052 ctx->pending_cx_data_sz += index_sz;
1053#ifdef TEST_SUPPLEMENTAL_SUPERFRAME_DATA
1054 index_sz += index_sz_test;
1055#endif
1056 }
1057 return index_sz;
1058}

1060static vpx_codec_frame_flags_t get_frame_pkt_flags(const VP9_COMP *cpi,
1061 unsigned int lib_flags) {
1062 vpx_codec_frame_flags_t flags = lib_flags << 16;
1063
1064 if (lib_flags & FRAMEFLAGS_KEY ||
1065 (cpi->use_svc && cpi->svc
1066 .layer_context[cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id *
1067 cpi->svc.number_temporal_layers +
1068 cpi->svc.temporal_layer_id]
1069 .is_key_frame))
1070 flags |= VPX_FRAME_IS_KEY;
1071
1072 if (cpi->droppable) flags |= VPX_FRAME_IS_DROPPABLE;
1073
1074 return flags;
1075}

1098const size_t kMinCompressedSize = 8192;
1099static vpx_codec_err_t encoder_encode(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
1100 const vpx_image_t *img,
1101 vpx_codec_pts_t pts_val,
1102 unsigned long duration,
1103 vpx_enc_frame_flags_t enc_flags,
1104 unsigned long deadline) {
1105 volatile vpx_codec_err_t res = VPX_CODEC_OK;
1106 volatile vpx_enc_frame_flags_t flags = enc_flags;
1107 volatile vpx_codec_pts_t pts = pts_val;
1108 VP9_COMP *const cpi = ctx->cpi;
1109 const vpx_rational64_t *const timestamp_ratio = &ctx->timestamp_ratio;
1110 size_t data_sz;
1111 vpx_codec_cx_pkt_t pkt;
1112 memset(&pkt, 0, sizeof(pkt));
1113
1114 if (cpi == NULL) return VPX_CODEC_INVALID_PARAM;
1115
1116 if (img != NULL) {
1117 res = validate_img(ctx, img);
1118 if (res == VPX_CODEC_OK) {
1119 // There's no codec control for multiple alt-refs so check the encoder
1120 // instance for its status to determine the compressed data size.
1121 data_sz = ctx->cfg.g_w * ctx->cfg.g_h * get_image_bps(img) / 8 *
1122 (cpi->multi_layer_arf ? 8 : 2);
1123 if (data_sz < kMinCompressedSize) data_sz = kMinCompressedSize;
1124 if (ctx->cx_data == NULL || ctx->cx_data_sz < data_sz) {
1125 ctx->cx_data_sz = data_sz;
1126 free(ctx->cx_data);
1127 ctx->cx_data = (unsigned char *)malloc(ctx->cx_data_sz);
1128 if (ctx->cx_data == NULL) {
1129 return VPX_CODEC_MEM_ERROR;
1130 }
1131 }
1132 }
1133 }
1134
1135 if (!ctx->pts_offset_initialized) {
1136 ctx->pts_offset = pts;
1137 ctx->pts_offset_initialized = 1;
1138 }
1139 pts -= ctx->pts_offset;
1140
1141 pick_quickcompress_mode(ctx, duration, deadline);
1142 vpx_codec_pkt_list_init(&ctx->pkt_list);
1143
1144 // Handle Flags
1145 if (((flags & VP8_EFLAG_NO_UPD_GF) && (flags & VP8_EFLAG_FORCE_GF)) ||
1146 ((flags & VP8_EFLAG_NO_UPD_ARF) && (flags & VP8_EFLAG_FORCE_ARF))) {
1147 ctx->base.err_detail = "Conflicting flags.";
1148 return VPX_CODEC_INVALID_PARAM;
1149 }
1150
1151 if (setjmp(cpi->common.error.jmp)) {
1152 cpi->common.error.setjmp = 0;
1153 res = update_error_state(ctx, &cpi->common.error);
1154 vpx_clear_system_state();
1155 return res;
1156 }
1157 cpi->common.error.setjmp = 1;
1158
1159 if (res == VPX_CODEC_OK) vp9_apply_encoding_flags(cpi, flags);
1160
1161 // Handle fixed keyframe intervals
1162 if (ctx->cfg.kf_mode == VPX_KF_AUTO &&
1163 ctx->cfg.kf_min_dist == ctx->cfg.kf_max_dist) {
1164 if (++ctx->fixed_kf_cntr > ctx->cfg.kf_min_dist) {
1165 flags |= VPX_EFLAG_FORCE_KF;
1166 ctx->fixed_kf_cntr = 1;
1167 }
1168 }
1169
1170 if (res == VPX_CODEC_OK) {
1171 unsigned int lib_flags = 0;
1172 YV12_BUFFER_CONFIG sd;
1173 int64_t dst_time_stamp = timebase_units_to_ticks(timestamp_ratio, pts);
1174 int64_t dst_end_time_stamp =
1175 timebase_units_to_ticks(timestamp_ratio, pts + duration);
1176 size_t size, cx_data_sz;
1177 unsigned char *cx_data;
1178
1179 cpi->svc.timebase_fac = timebase_units_to_ticks(timestamp_ratio, 1);
1180 cpi->svc.time_stamp_superframe = dst_time_stamp;
1181
1182 // Set up internal flags
1183 if (ctx->base.init_flags & VPX_CODEC_USE_PSNR) cpi->b_calculate_psnr = 1;
1184
1185 if (img != NULL) {
1186 res = image2yuvconfig(img, &sd);
1187
1188 // Store the original flags in to the frame buffer. Will extract the
1189 // key frame flag when we actually encode this frame.
1190 if (vp9_receive_raw_frame(cpi, flags | ctx->next_frame_flags, &sd,
1191 dst_time_stamp, dst_end_time_stamp)) {
1192 res = update_error_state(ctx, &cpi->common.error);
1193 }
1194 ctx->next_frame_flags = 0;
1195 }
1196
1197 cx_data = ctx->cx_data;
1198 cx_data_sz = ctx->cx_data_sz;
1199
1200 /* Any pending invisible frames? */
1201 if (ctx->pending_cx_data) {
1202 memmove(cx_data, ctx->pending_cx_data, ctx->pending_cx_data_sz);
1203 ctx->pending_cx_data = cx_data;
1204 cx_data += ctx->pending_cx_data_sz;
1205 cx_data_sz -= ctx->pending_cx_data_sz;
1206
1207 /* TODO: this is a minimal check, the underlying codec doesn't respect
1208 * the buffer size anyway.
1209 */
1210 if (cx_data_sz < ctx->cx_data_sz / 2) {
1211 vpx_internal_error(&cpi->common.error, VPX_CODEC_ERROR,
1212 "Compressed data buffer too small");
1213 return VPX_CODEC_ERROR;
1214 }
1215 }
1216
1217 if (cpi->oxcf.pass == 1 && !cpi->use_svc) {
1218#if !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
1219 // compute first pass stats
1220 if (img) {
1221 int ret;
1222 vpx_codec_cx_pkt_t fps_pkt;
1223 ENCODE_FRAME_RESULT encode_frame_result;
1224 vp9_init_encode_frame_result(&encode_frame_result);
1225 // TODO(angiebird): Call vp9_first_pass directly
1226 ret = vp9_get_compressed_data(cpi, &lib_flags, &size, cx_data,
1227 &dst_time_stamp, &dst_end_time_stamp,
1228 !img, &encode_frame_result);
1229 assert(size == 0); // There is no compressed data in the first pass
1230 (void)ret;
1231 assert(ret == 0);
1232 fps_pkt = get_first_pass_stats_pkt(&cpi->twopass.this_frame_stats);
1233 vpx_codec_pkt_list_add(&ctx->pkt_list.head, &fps_pkt);
1234 } else {
1235 if (!cpi->twopass.first_pass_done) {
1236 vpx_codec_cx_pkt_t fps_pkt;
1237 vp9_end_first_pass(cpi);
1238 fps_pkt = get_first_pass_stats_pkt(&cpi->twopass.total_stats);
1239 vpx_codec_pkt_list_add(&ctx->pkt_list.head, &fps_pkt);
1240 }
1241 }
1242#else // !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
1243 assert(0);
1244#endif // !CONFIG_REALTIME_ONLY
1245 } else {
1246 ENCODE_FRAME_RESULT encode_frame_result;
1247 vp9_init_encode_frame_result(&encode_frame_result);
1248 while (cx_data_sz >= ctx->cx_data_sz / 2 &&
1249 -1 != vp9_get_compressed_data(cpi, &lib_flags, &size, cx_data,
1250 &dst_time_stamp, &dst_end_time_stamp,
1251 !img, &encode_frame_result)) {
1252 // Pack psnr pkt
1253 if (size > 0 && !cpi->use_svc) {
1254 // TODO(angiebird): Figure out while we don't need psnr pkt when
1255 // use_svc is on
1256 PSNR_STATS psnr;
1257 if (vp9_get_psnr(cpi, &psnr)) {
1258 vpx_codec_cx_pkt_t psnr_pkt = get_psnr_pkt(&psnr);
1259 vpx_codec_pkt_list_add(&ctx->pkt_list.head, &psnr_pkt);
1260 }
1261 }
1262
1263 if (size || (cpi->use_svc && cpi->svc.skip_enhancement_layer)) {
1264 // Pack invisible frames with the next visible frame
1265 if (!cpi->common.show_frame ||
1266 (cpi->use_svc && cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id <
1267 cpi->svc.number_spatial_layers - 1)) {
1268 if (ctx->pending_cx_data == 0) ctx->pending_cx_data = cx_data;
1269 ctx->pending_cx_data_sz += size;
1270 if (size)
1271 ctx->pending_frame_sizes[ctx->pending_frame_count++] = size;
1272 ctx->pending_frame_magnitude |= size;
1273 cx_data += size;
1274 cx_data_sz -= size;
1275 pkt.data.frame.width[cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id] = cpi->common.width;
1276 pkt.data.frame.height[cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id] =
1277 cpi->common.height;
1278 pkt.data.frame.spatial_layer_encoded[cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id] =
1279 1 - cpi->svc.drop_spatial_layer[cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id];
1280
1281 if (ctx->output_cx_pkt_cb.output_cx_pkt) {
1282 pkt.kind = VPX_CODEC_CX_FRAME_PKT;
1283 pkt.data.frame.pts =
1284 ticks_to_timebase_units(timestamp_ratio, dst_time_stamp) +
1285 ctx->pts_offset;
1286 pkt.data.frame.duration = (unsigned long)ticks_to_timebase_units(
1287 timestamp_ratio, dst_end_time_stamp - dst_time_stamp);
1288 pkt.data.frame.flags = get_frame_pkt_flags(cpi, lib_flags);
1289 pkt.data.frame.buf = ctx->pending_cx_data;
1290 pkt.data.frame.sz = size;
1291 ctx->pending_cx_data = NULL;
1292 ctx->pending_cx_data_sz = 0;
1293 ctx->pending_frame_count = 0;
1294 ctx->pending_frame_magnitude = 0;
1295 ctx->output_cx_pkt_cb.output_cx_pkt(
1296 &pkt, ctx->output_cx_pkt_cb.user_priv);
1297 }
1298 continue;
1299 }
1300
1301 // Add the frame packet to the list of returned packets.
1302 pkt.kind = VPX_CODEC_CX_FRAME_PKT;
1303 pkt.data.frame.pts =
1304 ticks_to_timebase_units(timestamp_ratio, dst_time_stamp) +
1305 ctx->pts_offset;
1306 pkt.data.frame.duration = (unsigned long)ticks_to_timebase_units(
1307 timestamp_ratio, dst_end_time_stamp - dst_time_stamp);
1308 pkt.data.frame.flags = get_frame_pkt_flags(cpi, lib_flags);
1309 pkt.data.frame.width[cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id] = cpi->common.width;
1310 pkt.data.frame.height[cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id] = cpi->common.height;
1311 pkt.data.frame.spatial_layer_encoded[cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id] =
1312 1 - cpi->svc.drop_spatial_layer[cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id];
1313
1314 if (ctx->pending_cx_data) {
1315 if (size)
1316 ctx->pending_frame_sizes[ctx->pending_frame_count++] = size;
1317 ctx->pending_frame_magnitude |= size;
1318 ctx->pending_cx_data_sz += size;
1319 // write the superframe only for the case when
1320 if (!ctx->output_cx_pkt_cb.output_cx_pkt)
1321 size += write_superframe_index(ctx);
1322 pkt.data.frame.buf = ctx->pending_cx_data;
1323 pkt.data.frame.sz = ctx->pending_cx_data_sz;
1324 ctx->pending_cx_data = NULL;
1325 ctx->pending_cx_data_sz = 0;
1326 ctx->pending_frame_count = 0;
1327 ctx->pending_frame_magnitude = 0;
1328 } else {
1329 pkt.data.frame.buf = cx_data;
1330 pkt.data.frame.sz = size;
1331 }
1332 pkt.data.frame.partition_id = -1;
1333
1334 if (ctx->output_cx_pkt_cb.output_cx_pkt)
1335 ctx->output_cx_pkt_cb.output_cx_pkt(
1336 &pkt, ctx->output_cx_pkt_cb.user_priv);
1337 else
1338 vpx_codec_pkt_list_add(&ctx->pkt_list.head, &pkt);
1339
1340 cx_data += size;
1341 cx_data_sz -= size;
1342 if (is_one_pass_cbr_svc(cpi) &&
1343 (cpi->svc.spatial_layer_id ==
1344 cpi->svc.number_spatial_layers - 1)) {
1345 // Encoded all spatial layers; exit loop.
1346 break;
1347 }
1348 }
1349 }
1350 }
1351 }
1352
1353 cpi->common.error.setjmp = 0;
1354 return res;
1355}

1498static vpx_codec_err_t ctrl_set_svc(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx, va_list args) {
1499 int data = va_arg(args, int);
1500 const vpx_codec_enc_cfg_t *cfg = &ctx->cfg;
1501 // Both one-pass and two-pass RC are supported now.
1502 // User setting this has to make sure of the following.
1503 // In two-pass setting: either (but not both)
1504 // cfg->ss_number_layers > 1, or cfg->ts_number_layers > 1
1505 // In one-pass setting:
1506 // either or both cfg->ss_number_layers > 1, or cfg->ts_number_layers > 1
1507
1508 vp9_set_svc(ctx->cpi, data);
1509
1510 if (data == 1 &&
1511 (cfg->g_pass == VPX_RC_FIRST_PASS || cfg->g_pass == VPX_RC_LAST_PASS) &&
1512 cfg->ss_number_layers > 1 && cfg->ts_number_layers > 1) {
1513 return VPX_CODEC_INVALID_PARAM;
1514 }
1515
1516 vp9_set_row_mt(ctx->cpi);
1517
1518 return VPX_CODEC_OK;
1519}

1558static vpx_codec_err_t ctrl_set_svc_parameters(vpx_codec_alg_priv_t *ctx,
1559 va_list args) {
1560 VP9_COMP *const cpi = ctx->cpi;
1561 vpx_svc_extra_cfg_t *const params = va_arg(args, vpx_svc_extra_cfg_t *);
1562 int sl, tl;
1563
1564 // Number of temporal layers and number of spatial layers have to be set
1565 // properly before calling this control function.
1566 for (sl = 0; sl < cpi->svc.number_spatial_layers; ++sl) {
1567 for (tl = 0; tl < cpi->svc.number_temporal_layers; ++tl) {
1568 const int layer =
1569 LAYER_IDS_TO_IDX(sl, tl, cpi->svc.number_temporal_layers);
1570 LAYER_CONTEXT *lc = &cpi->svc.layer_context[layer];
1571 lc->max_q = params->max_quantizers[layer];
1572 lc->min_q = params->min_quantizers[layer];
1573 lc->scaling_factor_num = params->scaling_factor_num[sl];
1574 lc->scaling_factor_den = params->scaling_factor_den[sl];
1575 lc->speed = params->speed_per_layer[sl];
1576 lc->loopfilter_ctrl = params->loopfilter_ctrl[sl];
1577 }

1950
1951VP9EncoderConfig vp9_get_encoder_config(int frame_width, int frame_height,
1952 vpx_rational_t frame_rate,
1953 int target_bitrate, int encode_speed,
1954 vpx_enc_pass enc_pass) {
1955 /* This function will generate the same VP9EncoderConfig used by the
1956 * vpxenc command given below.
1957 * The configs in the vpxenc command corresponds to parameters of
1958 * vp9_get_encoder_config() as follows.
1959 *
1960 * WIDTH: frame_width
1961 * HEIGHT: frame_height
1962 * FPS: frame_rate
1963 * BITRATE: target_bitrate
1964 * CPU_USED:encode_speed
1965 *
1966 * INPUT, OUTPUT, LIMIT will not affect VP9EncoderConfig
1967 *
1968 * vpxenc command:
1969 * INPUT=bus_cif.y4m
1970 * OUTPUT=output.webm
1971 * WIDTH=352
1972 * HEIGHT=288
1973 * BITRATE=600
1974 * FPS=30/1
1975 * LIMIT=150
1976 * CPU_USED=0
1977 * ./vpxenc --limit=$LIMIT --width=$WIDTH --height=$HEIGHT --fps=$FPS
1978 * --lag-in-frames=25 \
1979 * --codec=vp9 --good --cpu-used=CPU_USED --threads=0 --profile=0 \
1980 * --min-q=0 --max-q=63 --auto-alt-ref=1 --passes=2 --kf-max-dist=150 \
1981 * --kf-min-dist=0 --drop-frame=0 --static-thresh=0 --bias-pct=50 \
1982 * --minsection-pct=0 --maxsection-pct=150 --arnr-maxframes=7 --psnr \
1983 * --arnr-strength=5 --sharpness=0 --undershoot-pct=100 --overshoot-pct=100 \
1984 * --frame-parallel=0 --tile-columns=0 --cpu-used=0 --end-usage=vbr \
1985 * --target-bitrate=$BITRATE -o $OUTPUT $INPUT
1986 */
1987
1988 VP9EncoderConfig oxcf;
1989 vp9_extracfg extra_cfg = get_extra_cfg();
1990 vpx_codec_enc_cfg_t enc_cfg = get_enc_cfg(
1991 frame_width, frame_height, frame_rate, target_bitrate, enc_pass);
1992 set_encoder_config(&oxcf, &enc_cfg, &extra_cfg);
1993
1994 // These settings are made to match the settings of the vpxenc command.
1995 oxcf.key_freq = 150;
1996 oxcf.under_shoot_pct = 100;
1997 oxcf.over_shoot_pct = 100;
1998 oxcf.max_threads = 0;
1999 oxcf.tile_columns = 0;
2000 oxcf.frame_parallel_decoding_mode = 0;
2001 oxcf.two_pass_vbrmax_section = 150;
2002 oxcf.speed = abs(encode_speed);
2003 return oxcf;
2004}
